# Android cross-compile probe -- Phase 2 Task 8
#
# Command:
#   GOOS=android GOARCH=arm64 CGO_ENABLED=0 GOWORK=off go build ./...
#
# Result on feature/android-phase-2 prior to the cmd/graywolf stub commit:
#   exit 0 -- entire module already cross-compiles cleanly.
#
# Why it was already clean:
#   - pkg/pttdevice already ships paired build tags
#     (cm108_linux.go / cm108_modem.go via !linux, sysfs_other.go,
#     gpio_lines_linux.go / gpio_lines_other.go, enumerate_nonwindows.go).
#   - pkg/gps and the rest of pkg/* are pure Go with no host syscalls
#     that GOOS=android rejects.
#   - pkg/platformsvc is intentionally //go:build android only
#     (per spec section 4.3 and the "Build-tagged stubs" gotcha at
#     line 477 of .context/2026-05-09-android-phase-2-spec.md), so it
#     ONLY compiles on android -- exactly the inverse of the
#     cmd/graywolf desktop entry.
#   - cmd/graywolf, cmd/graywolf-pocb, cmd/flareschema-gen,
#     cmd/smoke-kiss-tcp-client all happen to use only cross-portable
#     stdlib + project deps.
#
# `go list ./...` under GOOS=android returns 59 packages cleanly.
#
# What Task 8 still adds (so phase 3 has a clean swap-in point):
#   - cmd/graywolf/main.go gets //go:build !android so the desktop
#     entry stays explicitly non-android-targeted.
#   - cmd/graywolf/main_android.go is a one-line `func main() {}`
#     stub gated //go:build android; phase 3 replaces it with the
#     real Android entry that wires pkg/platformsvc + pkg/gps/android
#     + pkg/pttdevice/android into the app graph.
#
# Post-stub probe (final):
#   GOOS=android GOARCH=arm64 CGO_ENABLED=0 GOWORK=off go build ./...
#   exit 0 -- BUILD CLEAN.
#
# Desktop verification:
#   GOWORK=off go build ./...    -> exit 0
#   GOWORK=off go test ./...     -> all packages PASS
#                                   (pkg/platformsvc has no desktop
#                                    files, so it's silently skipped
#                                    on desktop; cross-compile of its
#                                    test binary verified separately
#                                    with `go test -c` for android.)
